headline: Major U.S. Stock Indexes Gain; Intel Rises on Nvidia Investment
summary: The Dow industrials, S&P 500 and Nasdaq all rose as Nvidia’s deal to invest in Intel added fuel to the tech rally.

headline: Stocks Climb to Records Again
summary: The S&P 500, Nasdaq and Dow industrials all closed at record highs Thursday, the day after the Fed moved to cut interest rates.  “It looks to me like an after-the-fact rate-cut rally,” said Jason Pride, chief of investment strategy and research at Glenmede.  The Nasdaq Composite gained almost a full percentage point to reach its 27th record close of 2025.

headline: FOMC Meeting: What Does the Federal Reserve’s September Rate Cut Mean for Bitcoin?
summary: The Federal Reserve is back in focus as today’s Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC) meeting could bring the first rate cut of 2025, and traders are closely watching what it could mean for the Bitcoin price. headline: Bitcoin price climbs above $117K after Fed interest rate cut
summary: Bitcoin extended gains on Thursday after the Federal Reserve cut interest rates by 25 basis points, its first reduction in nine months.
